cs.SE, cs.HC, cs.DB, cs.CY, cs.PL 

This paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category as it deals with spreadsheet errors and proposes a new taxonomy for classifying negative spreadsheet-related phenomena. It also involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it requires knowledge about the "brain state" of spreadsheet users. Additionally, it may fall under the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category as spreadsheets are often used to manage data. The paper also touches upon cybersecurity (cs.CY) as faulty spreadsheets can lead to security breaches. Finally, it may be relevant to Programming Languages (cs.PL) as spreadsheets can be seen as a form of programming.
